---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import { assets } from '../data/assets';
---
<MainLayout title="About | Corrine J Blackthorn">
  <section>
    <div class="container split">
      <div class="portrait-frame"><img src={assets.portraits[1]} alt="Corrine J Blackthorn portrait" /></div>
      <div>
        <span class="kicker">My Story</span>
        <h1>Compassion, resilience, and radical honesty.</h1>
        <p>I am a technologist, creator, advocate, entrepreneur, writer, photographer, musician, baker, and lifelong learner. More than any title, though, I am someone who believes deeply in helping people feel seen, inspired, and curious.</p>
        <p>My life has never followed a straight path. I grew up feeling different long before I had all the words to explain why, and that shaped the way I see people, systems, and the world around me.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section><div class="container"><div class="section-heading"><span class="kicker">Becoming</span><h2>The woman I became.</h2><p>As an autistic person, I have often experienced the world differently than the people around me.</p><p>Those differences taught me resilience, but they also taught me empathy for anyone who has ever felt like they did not quite belong.</p><p>Over the years, I have survived homelessness, abuse, loss, and more challenges than I can easily count. Those experiences changed me, but they never took away my belief in people. If anything, they strengthened it.</p></div></div></section>
  <section class="quote-band"><div class="container"><blockquote>Compassion is not weakness. It is courage.</blockquote></div></section>
  <section><div class="container split"><div><span class="kicker">Grandma</span><h2>Compassion was modeled for me.</h2><p>Much of who I am today was shaped by my grandmother.</p><p>The values she modeled continue to guide every part of my work and life.</p></div><div class="portrait-frame"><img src={assets.portraits[2]} alt="Corrine J Blackthorn" loading="lazy" /></div></div></section>
  <section><div class="container"><div class="section-heading"><span class="kicker">Identity</span><h2>Radical transparency and honesty.</h2><p>One of the longest journeys I have ever taken was accepting that I am transgender.</p><p>Transition was not about becoming someone else. It was about finally allowing myself to become who I had always been.</p></div></div></section>
  <section><div class="container"><div class="section-heading"><span class="kicker">Work</span><h2>Technology, creativity, and advocacy.</h2><p>Professionally, I have built a career in information security, identity and access management, systems engineering, governance, and technology leadership.</p><p>Creatively, I write, photograph, bake, and create music.</p><p>Advocacy is equally important to me.</p></div></div></section>
  <section class="quote-band"><div class="container"><blockquote>Blackthorn is not just a name. It is the thread connecting every project, story, photograph, song, and act of advocacy I create.</blockquote></div></section>
  <section><div class="container"><div class="section-heading"><span class="kicker">Why Blackthorn</span><h2>Strength, edge, and resilience.</h2><p>The name Blackthorn came during my transition.</p></div><div class="grid"><article class="card"><h3>Seen</h3><p>I care about the people who are overlooked.</p></article><article class="card"><h3>Inspired</h3><p>I believe stories, images, music, food, and technology can help people imagine something better.</p></article><article class="card"><h3>Curious</h3><p>Curiosity keeps us learning, growing, rebuilding, and finding new paths forward.</p></article></div></div></section>
  <section><div class="container"><div class="section-heading"><span class="kicker">Continue Exploring</span><h2>Different paths, shared purpose.</h2><p>If you'd like to learn more about my work, creativity, and projects, start here.</p></div><div class="grid"><a class="card" href="/technology/"><h3>Technology</h3><p>Identity, security, systems, and leadership.</p></a><a class="card" href="/writing/"><h3>Writing</h3><p>Field notes, memoir, essays, and publications.</p></a><a class="card" href="/photography/"><h3>Photography</h3><p>Visual storytelling and everyday beauty.</p></a><a class="card" href="/music/"><h3>Music</h3><p>Glass & Thorns and creative expression.</p></a><a class="card" href="/projects/"><h3>Projects</h3><p>The things I'm building.</p></a></div></div></section>
  <section class="quote-band"><div class="container"><blockquote>I hope they remember that I cared. I hope they remember that I fought for people who could not always fight for themselves.</blockquote></div></section>
</MainLayout>